ently receives fiber allocation for just ~30% of its targets.\nHowever, we estimate that our photometric cuts are > 95% complete in target\nselection at z < 0.03 between 19 <r < 21. The full five-year DESI program will\nexpand the LOW-Z sample, densely mapping the low-redshift Universe and\nproviding critical information about how to pursue effective and efficient\nlow-redshift surveys.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 14 Dec 2022 19:00:00 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-12-16"}
